-Okay.

00:03:20.555 --> 00:03:22.849
-How's the braised kimchi stew?
-I'd say B-minus.

00:03:23.642 --> 00:03:25.268
I guess you're getting old too.

00:03:25.352 --> 00:03:27.938
You used to season it perfectly before.

00:03:29.022 --> 00:03:32.192
I heard the side dish stores
do morning deliveries every day.

00:03:34.277 --> 00:03:36.863
I just don't want you to work too hard.

00:03:36.947 --> 00:03:38.573
It's good. It's not bad.

00:03:38.657 --> 00:03:40.909
Do you also not like it?

00:03:44.371 --> 00:03:46.289
-I like it. It's delicious.
-Okay.

00:03:46.373 --> 00:03:48.959
He eats just about anything.
No wonder he's so tall.

00:03:56.216 --> 00:03:59.594
Son, you and your friends
must talk about it, right?

00:04:00.262 --> 00:04:03.348
"Just one more shot, and we could get
into Seoul National University."

00:04:03.431 --> 00:04:04.850
-Right?
-No, we don't.

00:04:07.602 --> 00:04:08.687
No one says that?

00:04:08.770 --> 00:04:11.773
They all seem happy.
They also said the campus is pretty.

00:04:14.442 --> 00:04:15.902
-How about you?
-I feel the same.

00:04:22.534 --> 00:04:23.952
Don't we have plain barley tea?

00:04:24.035 --> 00:04:26.538
Why do you keep steeping things
in the water?

00:04:27.163 --> 00:04:28.415
It's good for you.

00:04:28.498 --> 00:04:30.709
It's sour.

00:04:40.927 --> 00:04:42.762
-I'm off.
-Okay.

00:04:43.388 --> 00:04:44.264
Let's go.

00:04:47.183 --> 00:04:49.477
-Bye, Mom.
-Wait.

00:04:49.561 --> 00:04:50.687
Hang on a minute.

00:04:51.730 --> 00:04:54.399
Wait for me. I'll go with you.

00:04:57.569 --> 00:04:59.404
It's a good day.

00:05:05.452 --> 00:05:06.828
Let me.

00:05:06.912 --> 00:05:08.955
Gosh. Thank you.

00:05:10.248 --> 00:05:12.250
Why can't you throw it out
before it piles up?

