EXCELLENCE AWARD
KIM NAK-SU

00:12:01.075 --> 00:12:02.160
GENERAL MANAGER KIM NAK-SU

00:12:02.243 --> 00:12:04.704
Mr. Baek's bag is

00:12:04.787 --> 00:12:06.748
not this one.

00:12:07.290 --> 00:12:10.084
Is it this one? No.

00:12:10.168 --> 00:12:11.377
Found it.

00:12:13.171 --> 00:12:14.714
Three million won?

00:12:17.133 --> 00:12:19.510
I'll just think of it
as my early promotion present.

00:12:19.594 --> 00:12:23.973
But I'll buy something a little cheaper.
Around two million won.

00:12:29.020 --> 00:12:30.605
-Good morning, Mr. Kim.
-Hello.

00:12:30.688 --> 00:12:32.565
Good morning.

00:12:33.316 --> 00:12:34.859
I guess you stopped by a cafe.

00:12:35.777 --> 00:12:36.736
Yes,

00:12:36.819 --> 00:12:39.113
we ran into each other at the station
and stopped by one.

00:12:39.197 --> 00:12:41.032
Did you now?

00:12:41.115 --> 00:12:44.827
We all know
you prefer the instant coffee mix anyway.

00:12:44.911 --> 00:12:47.872
Wrong. I enjoy regular coffee
if someone buys me one.

00:12:47.955 --> 00:12:49.832
I'll remember that!

00:12:49.916 --> 00:12:51.084
It's three minutes

00:12:51.626 --> 00:12:52.752
past 9:00.

00:12:56.589 --> 00:12:57.507
I apologize.

00:12:57.590 --> 00:12:58.466
-Sorry, sir.
-Sorry.

00:12:58.549 --> 00:13:01.844
The staff lounge is stocked
with Starbucks capsules.

00:13:01.928 --> 00:13:04.764
Shouldn't you show
a little more interest in the company?

00:13:10.186 --> 00:13:12.522
-Sung-gu!
-Assistant Manager Jung Sung-gu!

00:13:12.605 --> 00:13:14.315
How much did you pay for your bag?

00:13:16.359 --> 00:13:18.194
-This one?
-Yes.

00:13:21.447 --> 00:13:22.490
You mean the price?

00:13:22.573 --> 00:13:23.533
Yes.

00:13:24.909 --> 00:13:25.785
It's…

00:13:25.868 --> 00:13:26.953
It's 2.5 million won.

00:13:27.036 --> 00:13:28.496
Two point…

00:13:29.705 --> 00:13:30.665
Two point…

00:13:31.416 --> 00:13:33.000
I'm sorry. A bit excessive, isn't it?

00:13:33.084 --> 00:13:35.503
No, I didn't mean that.

00:13:35.586 --> 00:13:38.589
A bag like that isn't surprising
for a big-company assistant manager.

00:13:38.673 --> 00:13:40.967
Good morning to you all!

00:13:41.050 --> 00:13:42.218
-Good morning.
-Good morning.

00:13:42.301 --> 00:13:43.302
Hello, sir.

00:13:43.386 --> 00:13:44.637
-Hello.
-Hi.

00:13:45.263 --> 00:13:47.557
SALES DIRECTOR
BAEK JEONG-TAE (EMPLOYED 27 YEARS)

00:13:47.640 --> 00:13:49.392
-Nak-su.
-Yes, sir.

00:13:49.475 --> 00:13:50.435
Right.

00:13:51.352 --> 00:13:53.104
Have another happy day, everyone!

00:13:53.187 --> 00:13:54.522
-Bye, sir.
-Bye, sir.

00:13:54.605 --> 00:13:56.107
-Bye, sir.
-Sir.

00:13:57.608 --> 00:13:58.776
Come in.

00:14:00.403 --> 00:14:01.279
Take a seat.

00:14:08.744 --> 00:14:09.912
Hello, Jin-woo.

00:14:10.413 --> 00:14:11.456
Hello.

00:14:15.751 --> 00:14:17.086
-Nak-su.
-Yes.

00:14:17.170 --> 00:14:20.131
On Saturday, the sales directors
of the three major telecoms

00:14:20.214 --> 00:14:21.215
are having a golf round.

00:14:21.299 --> 00:14:23.426
"Saturday golf with the major three."

00:14:23.509 --> 00:14:25.970
-So the big issue that day will be…
-Yes, sir.

00:14:26.053 --> 00:14:29.182
It looks like the government will continue
to tighten its budget.

00:14:29.265 --> 00:14:32.768
And if the three companies engage
in a bidding war for every public tender,

00:14:32.852 --> 00:14:34.228
we'll wipe ourselves out.

00:14:34.312 --> 00:14:36.522
-It--
-Right. It's all cutthroat these days.

00:14:36.606 --> 00:14:38.107
Exactly.

00:14:38.191 --> 00:14:40.443
To put it nicely, it's like a social club.

00:14:40.526 --> 00:14:41.986
"Like a social club."

00:14:42.069 --> 00:14:44.864
If we let L win the bid
for this upcoming project…

00:14:44.947 --> 00:14:46.991
-"Win bid."
-…we'll take the next Ministry deal.

00:14:47.074 --> 00:14:48.409
"We'll take it."

00:14:49.160 --> 00:14:51.037
Then we'll let T have the next deal.

00:14:51.120 --> 00:14:52.788
"T will have the next deal."

00:14:52.872 --> 00:14:54.373
That's so distracting.

00:14:55.458 --> 00:14:57.084
Just say it in your head.

00:14:58.294 --> 00:14:59.170
I'm sorry, sir.

00:15:00.171 --> 00:15:01.756
It's a very important meeting.

00:15:02.381 --> 00:15:03.674
Which one of you will…

00:15:05.092 --> 00:15:07.929
I'll oversee everything, Mr. Baek.

00:15:12.808 --> 00:15:14.352
-Jin-woo, you can…
-Yes, sir.

00:15:15.061 --> 00:15:16.521
If you'll excuse me.

00:15:16.604 --> 00:15:18.898
-Sure.
-Bye.

00:15:21.984 --> 00:15:23.110
My gosh.

00:15:25.112 --> 00:15:26.989
What was that all about? Let me handle it.

00:15:27.073 --> 00:15:28.991
You two should do it together.
It's a big job.

00:15:29.075 --> 00:15:31.953
How can I work with a guy who drags
his slippers into the boss's office?

00:15:32.036 --> 00:15:34.163
-I can handle--
-Do you enter this room

00:15:34.830 --> 00:15:36.624
when I'm not here?

00:15:39.001 --> 00:15:42.421
I only came to check if you were in early

00:15:42.505 --> 00:15:44.465
and to say hello.

00:15:44.549 --> 00:15:46.050
-Nak-su.
-Yes.

00:15:46.133 --> 00:15:49.095
Honestly, I'd rather
have my guy get promoted

00:15:49.178 --> 00:15:51.305
to managing director over Do Jin-woo.

00:15:52.056 --> 00:15:53.307
I mean it.

00:15:53.391 --> 00:15:54.350
Yes.

00:15:54.433 --> 00:15:57.270
Keep yourself in check.
There are eyes on you everywhere.

00:15:58.271 --> 00:16:00.481
Do Jin-woo didn't mean to rat you out.

00:16:00.565 --> 00:16:02.149
He's looking out for you.

00:16:03.943 --> 00:16:07.446
That's not what…
I had something to tell you this morning--

00:16:07.530 --> 00:16:10.366
Just say sorry and be done with it,
for Christ's sake.

00:16:10.908 --> 00:16:11.784
Okay?

00:16:12.326 --> 00:16:13.995
I'm sorry.

00:16:15.788 --> 00:16:18.791
And how come your team members
arrive to work at the same time as me?

00:16:18.874 --> 00:16:21.210
Jin-woo's team is always ready to go.

00:16:21.836 --> 00:16:25.089
Your people always
just barely make it by 9:00.

00:16:25.172 --> 00:16:27.049
I'll have a talk with them.

00:16:27.133 --> 00:16:28.759
"Punctuality."

00:16:30.219 --> 00:16:32.305
And pick me up for golf on Saturday.

00:16:32.388 --> 00:16:33.639
"Pick up on Saturday."

00:16:35.516 --> 00:16:37.310
You know my new address, right?

00:16:37.393 --> 00:16:40.062
Yes, of course. Banpo River Palace.

00:16:40.146 --> 00:16:41.188
It's Building 103.

00:16:41.272 --> 00:16:44.275
-"Building 103."
-For heaven's sake.

00:16:45.526 --> 00:16:47.361
I keep forgetting things these days.

00:16:49.447 --> 00:16:51.616
Pick Jin-woo up on your way to my house.

00:16:52.158 --> 00:16:54.493
You want me to pick Jin-woo up?

00:16:54.577 --> 00:16:56.579
It's better than moving around
in two or three cars.

00:16:56.662 --> 00:16:58.122
After all, we'll be drinking.

00:16:59.624 --> 00:17:02.668
What now? You don't feel
like giving your junior a ride?

00:17:03.544 --> 00:17:06.922
Not at all. I'll do that.

00:17:11.802 --> 00:17:12.887
Mr. Kim.

00:17:14.847 --> 00:17:16.932
Tattle-tale, tattle-tale, tattling again!

00:17:17.600 --> 00:17:18.601
Pardon? What was that?

00:17:18.684 --> 00:17:20.144
Nothing.

00:17:21.729 --> 00:17:24.649
Mr. Baek told me
to pick you up this Saturday.

00:17:25.524 --> 00:17:27.485
I was just told that too, sir.

00:17:28.319 --> 00:17:31.072
-I'm sorry.
-Nothing to feel sorry about.

00:17:31.656 --> 00:17:34.533
I can just wake up
a little earlier, right?

00:17:35.117 --> 00:17:38.579
You'll be too tired. Let me drive.

00:17:40.748 --> 00:17:41.999
Don't bother.

00:17:42.083 --> 00:17:44.835
My car is bigger. I'll drive.

00:17:44.919 --> 00:17:47.338
Okay then.

00:17:47.963 --> 00:17:49.548
With so many eyes watching that day,

00:17:49.632 --> 00:17:52.885
it would be a lot better to take
your nice car rather than mine.

00:17:52.968 --> 00:17:55.304
It's not all about the size, though.

00:17:56.722 --> 00:17:58.182
He sure is young.

00:17:59.684 --> 00:18:00.685
What a beast.

00:18:02.144 --> 00:18:03.562
Look at it go.

00:18:04.188 --> 00:18:07.274
This isn't a robot.

00:18:07.358 --> 00:18:09.694
It's more like the boss.

00:18:09.777 --> 00:18:10.695
Hey!

00:18:10.778 --> 00:18:12.988
This is what I get for listening to you!

00:18:13.072 --> 00:18:15.950
Ha-jin, Robot Auntie didn't do
anything wrong.

00:18:16.033 --> 00:18:17.618
The problem is your old house.

00:18:17.702 --> 00:18:19.203
It works just fine for us, doesn't it?

00:18:19.286 --> 00:18:21.226
-Is she on vacation?
-Ha-jin.

00:18:21.326 --> 00:18:24.083
Get a contractor
and have the threshold removed.

00:18:24.166 --> 00:18:26.711
That will make the house
look bigger and everything.

00:18:26.794 --> 00:18:28.796
If that's all, I'm going.
I've got breakfast waiting.

