What is it with people and cafes?

00:23:20.212 --> 00:23:23.298
The staff lounge is stocked
with instant coffee mix and capsules.

00:23:23.382 --> 00:23:24.800
Let's just talk here. What is it?

00:23:28.846 --> 00:23:30.180
I'm going to Ulleungdo Island.

00:23:31.682 --> 00:23:32.850
On a trip?

00:23:33.392 --> 00:23:34.727
Why are you going so far?

00:23:37.229 --> 00:23:38.439
They told me to go.

00:23:38.981 --> 00:23:41.358
They told me to go manage the facilities.

00:23:42.568 --> 00:23:43.694
I've got a month left.

00:23:52.411 --> 00:23:54.246
Jeez, man.

00:23:55.831 --> 00:23:57.332
What am I going to do?

00:23:59.460 --> 00:24:01.420
Sir, I've got the briefcase.

00:24:01.503 --> 00:24:02.379
Okay.

00:24:07.968 --> 00:24:09.094
It's 2.6 million won,

00:24:09.178 --> 00:24:11.638
and it's made of calf leather.

00:24:13.724 --> 00:24:15.434
This should be good enough.

00:24:15.517 --> 00:24:16.977
Shall I hand it over then?

00:24:17.061 --> 00:24:18.854
Mr. Kim told us to handle it ourselves.

00:24:18.937 --> 00:24:21.106
Did he? That's done then. I'll send it.

00:24:21.190 --> 00:24:22.608
I'm not sure.

00:24:23.859 --> 00:24:24.943
I need to leave soon.

00:24:26.278 --> 00:24:28.030
There he is. Hello, Mr. Kim.

00:24:28.113 --> 00:24:29.656
Did you enjoy your lunch?

00:24:29.740 --> 00:24:30.949
-Yes.
-Here.

00:24:31.700 --> 00:24:32.576
For you.

00:24:33.994 --> 00:24:34.870
Mr. Kim.

00:24:34.953 --> 00:24:35.829
I'm going to send

00:24:35.913 --> 00:24:38.916
the Q2 and Q4 public institution
new business strategy presentation.

00:24:38.999 --> 00:24:40.918
I told you to handle it with Ik-hyeon.

00:24:41.001 --> 00:24:42.503
Can I really send it over?

00:24:43.629 --> 00:24:45.672
Please handle it on your own.

00:24:45.756 --> 00:24:47.758
Have a sense of ownership, will you?

00:24:49.009 --> 00:24:50.344
Mr. Kim,

00:24:50.427 --> 00:24:53.013
this is the very final version,
and it'll be difficult to revise it.

00:24:53.097 --> 00:24:55.933
The Managing Director and
the Executive Director will see it.

00:24:59.103 --> 00:25:00.479
Hey. Add a space.

00:25:00.562 --> 00:25:02.189
-Okay. A space?
-No, change a line.

00:25:02.272 --> 00:25:04.983
-An arrow.
-An arrow.

00:25:05.067 --> 00:25:06.401
From the top menu, under "Shapes."

00:25:06.485 --> 00:25:07.945
-Keep looking.
-Yes, sir.

00:25:08.028 --> 00:25:09.279
What's with this font?

00:25:09.363 --> 00:25:11.949
It stands out too much. Change it.

00:25:12.032 --> 00:25:13.909
-Okay.
-Not that one.

00:25:13.992 --> 00:25:15.452
Not that one.

00:25:15.536 --> 00:25:17.329
You must be busy. Why don't we handle--

00:25:17.412 --> 00:25:20.249
If you were good at your jobs,
I wouldn't be busy. What's with the red?

00:25:20.332 --> 00:25:21.375
It's just red.

00:25:22.376 --> 00:25:25.337
It's not the red we usually use.

00:25:25.420 --> 00:25:27.714
I think it is.

00:25:27.798 --> 00:25:28.924
Is it?

00:25:32.219 --> 00:25:33.095
Take a look.

00:25:33.762 --> 00:25:36.306
Do they look the same to you?

00:25:36.390 --> 00:25:37.516
Look.

00:25:38.058 --> 00:25:40.894
I think it looks a little different
because it's printed out.

00:25:43.981 --> 00:25:45.649
What if they're actually different?

00:25:45.732 --> 00:25:47.192
It's fixed. Shall I send it?

00:25:47.276 --> 00:25:48.318
-Wait.
-Okay.

00:25:48.402 --> 00:25:50.362
What if they're actually different?

00:25:50.445 --> 00:25:51.530
Here.

00:25:51.613 --> 00:25:54.241
Is this red the same as that red?

00:25:54.324 --> 00:25:55.200
Huh? The same?

00:25:55.284 --> 00:25:56.493
But I was thinking,

00:25:56.577 --> 00:25:58.579
maybe we could tone down

00:25:58.662 --> 00:26:01.790
-the red a little--
-Just say sorry and be done with it.

00:26:01.874 --> 00:26:03.834
What's with all the excuses?

00:26:03.917 --> 00:26:04.835
I'm sorry.

00:26:04.918 --> 00:26:06.378
-Sung-gu.
-Yes, sir.

00:26:06.461 --> 00:26:07.796
Train your junior right.

00:26:09.214 --> 00:26:10.465
I'm sorry.

00:26:12.718 --> 00:26:16.096
Team performance is judged
on details like this.

00:26:16.180 --> 00:26:19.850
Performance reviews are around the corner.
Stay on your toes, will you?

00:26:19.933 --> 00:26:21.894
-Mr. Kim.
-What?

00:26:23.312 --> 00:26:25.063
I have a half day, so I'll get going.

00:26:27.399 --> 00:26:29.943
Great timing. What are you talking about?

00:26:30.027 --> 00:26:31.278
I told you a week ago.

00:26:31.361 --> 00:26:32.905
When was that?

00:26:33.530 --> 00:26:35.032
It should be on your messenger app.

00:26:37.326 --> 00:26:38.493
Okay. Just go.

00:26:40.287 --> 00:26:41.580
See you tomorrow.

00:26:42.956 --> 00:26:45.417
-What are you doing? Found it?
-Yes, sir.

00:26:50.422 --> 00:26:52.633
Leaving his working colleagues…
Zero loyalty.

00:26:53.383 --> 00:26:56.220
Mr. Song already finished
his work yesterday.

00:27:00.057 --> 00:27:01.516
"Mr. Song"?

00:27:02.684 --> 00:27:05.062
Ik-hyeon definitely lacks loyalty.

00:27:05.145 --> 00:27:06.396
Right.

00:27:06.480 --> 00:27:08.690
Where on earth does he keep going to?

00:27:08.774 --> 00:27:10.734
He said he was going for some inspections.

00:27:10.817 --> 00:27:11.902
Infection? Is he sick?

00:27:15.239 --> 00:27:16.448
No, inspections.

00:27:17.199 --> 00:27:19.785
He's going to analyze
real estate properties on-site.

00:27:19.868 --> 00:27:21.119
Real estate?

00:27:21.203 --> 00:27:22.412
Yes.

00:27:22.496 --> 00:27:24.206
He does that during work hours?

00:27:30.003 --> 00:27:32.756
Doesn't he know there's
a real estate master right here?

00:27:33.382 --> 00:27:35.592
Look at the stock market these days.

00:27:35.676 --> 00:27:37.803
The blue chips are rocketing
through the roof,

00:27:37.886 --> 00:27:40.597
while the junk stocks
are crashing to the bottom.

00:27:40.681 --> 00:27:43.308
The gap between them
just keeps getting wider.

00:27:43.392 --> 00:27:44.559
Polarization.

00:27:44.643 --> 00:27:46.645
The same goes for housing prices.

00:27:46.728 --> 00:27:49.856
The saying "real estate never loses"
is a thing of the past.

00:27:49.940 --> 00:27:51.608
One smart property is all you need.

00:27:51.692 --> 00:27:52.901
One smart property.

00:27:52.985 --> 00:27:54.695
Okay. Sure.

00:27:55.988 --> 00:27:59.491
Come here, Su-gyeom,
my one and only smart son.

00:27:59.574 --> 00:28:02.661
Now that you're in college,
you should know stuff like this.

00:28:02.744 --> 00:28:04.538
Economics. Personal finance.

00:28:04.621 --> 00:28:07.332
Men must know things like this.

00:28:10.085 --> 00:28:13.171
You've been doing that for a while.
Just what are you doing?

00:28:13.255 --> 00:28:18.343
I'm making a door ramp for Robot Auntie.

00:28:18.427 --> 00:28:19.553
What's wrong with your mom?

00:28:19.636 --> 00:28:22.014
How much did you say you paid for it?

00:28:22.097 --> 00:28:23.974
It was 800,000 won.

00:28:24.057 --> 00:28:24.933
Eight hundred…

00:28:26.852 --> 00:28:30.188
I'm worried your mom has
some kind of shopping addiction.

00:28:30.272 --> 00:28:33.025
What's the point of me making money
if we don't save it?

00:28:34.401 --> 00:28:35.485
Gosh.

00:28:36.987 --> 00:28:38.989
What is it?

00:28:39.781 --> 00:28:41.867
Right.

00:28:42.576 --> 00:28:44.870
What was I going to say?

00:28:45.912 --> 00:28:47.831
-A smart--
-A smart property.

00:28:47.914 --> 00:28:49.916
Oh, right!

00:28:50.417 --> 00:28:54.338
We had no choice but to rent
before I became a general manager.

00:28:55.380 --> 00:28:57.424
Look at how much
this apartment's value has gone up.

00:28:57.507 --> 00:29:00.969
If we hadn't bought it back then,
we would've never been able to afford it.

00:29:01.053 --> 00:29:02.804
You did an excellent job, Dad.

00:29:02.888 --> 00:29:06.141
You remember what I said
when we were buying this apartment, right?

00:29:06.224 --> 00:29:07.684
When we were buying this apartment?

00:29:07.768 --> 00:29:08.769
Yes.

00:29:12.314 --> 00:29:14.941
You really want to buy this apartment?
Don't you watch the news?

00:29:15.025 --> 00:29:18.070
It's better to buy it
than to keep paying higher deposits.

00:29:18.153 --> 00:29:21.406
People say the cost of mid-tier places
in Seoul goes up as much as inflation.

00:29:21.490 --> 00:29:22.741
I've looked into it.

00:29:22.824 --> 00:29:25.535
They're all just saying
whatever they were paid to say.

00:29:25.619 --> 00:29:26.745
Do you buy what they say?

00:29:26.828 --> 00:29:29.915
How would they know if prices
will keep going up or not? Are they gods?

00:29:29.998 --> 00:29:32.084
Will they take responsibility
if the bubble bursts?

00:29:32.167 --> 00:29:34.628
Forget it. If you don't help me,

00:29:34.711 --> 00:29:37.089
I'll ask my parents for a loan
and buy the apartment.

00:29:37.172 --> 00:29:40.008
Goodness, do you hear yourself?
Are you out of your mind?

00:29:48.850 --> 00:29:50.185
I'm going to do it.

00:30:08.495 --> 00:30:10.539
It doesn't matter whose idea it was.

00:30:10.622 --> 00:30:14.835
In the end, it's your apartment,
bought with the money you earned.

00:30:15.502 --> 00:30:16.962
Well said.

00:30:18.046 --> 00:30:19.423
Yes, it's all thanks to you.

00:30:20.048 --> 00:30:22.092
-You're the best.
-You're the best, Dad.

00:30:22.175 --> 00:30:24.636
Our family is the best.

00:30:26.888 --> 00:30:28.932
MIYUM ART MUSEUM
7 P.M.

00:30:33.061 --> 00:30:36.565
Will you go up now, Robot Auntie?

00:30:36.648 --> 00:30:37.899
-Let's see.
-Enjoy, Dad.

00:30:37.983 --> 00:30:40.986
Let me see.

00:30:47.367 --> 00:30:49.035
They were being sarcastic, right?

00:30:53.874 --> 00:30:55.208
-Mr. Heo Tae-hwan?
-Yes!

00:30:55.292 --> 00:30:56.585
Come quickly.

00:30:56.668 --> 00:30:59.588
You didn't even tell me what's going on.
What's the rush?

00:30:59.671 --> 00:31:01.089
-Go over there.
-There?

00:31:01.173 --> 00:31:02.799
-You'll see.
-Okay.

00:31:02.883 --> 00:31:04.634
-Mr. Lee. Mr. Heo Tae-hwan?
-Sorry!

00:31:04.718 --> 00:31:06.386
I'm sorry. My apologies.

00:31:06.470 --> 00:31:07.888
I didn't know it was here.

00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:09.681
Give that to him.

