You need to know how to go in
and perform a basic inspection.

00:31:42.380 --> 00:31:44.591
If islanders lose communication
in an emergency,

00:31:44.674 --> 00:31:46.551
will you take responsibility?

00:31:47.177 --> 00:31:48.178
Climb down.

00:31:51.431 --> 00:31:55.727
RESTRICTED AREA

00:31:57.270 --> 00:32:00.190
That's why I said to wear sneakers.

00:32:00.732 --> 00:32:02.317
Everyone else did. Didn't you tell him?

00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:03.693
I did.

00:32:12.827 --> 00:32:14.204
It's been five minutes. Hurry.

00:32:14.287 --> 00:32:15.372
Okay!

00:32:16.831 --> 00:32:17.999
Next person, get ready.

00:32:46.278 --> 00:32:47.988
Hello, Mr. Kim!

00:32:49.197 --> 00:32:50.073
Hello.

00:32:53.660 --> 00:32:56.162
It's a used car.

00:32:56.246 --> 00:32:57.998
But it's covered in plastic.

00:32:58.081 --> 00:32:59.958
That's because

00:33:00.917 --> 00:33:04.296
I bought some and put it on,
so it could feel like a new car.

00:33:04.879 --> 00:33:06.464
Do people really do that?

00:33:06.548 --> 00:33:08.425
Your car is fully decked out.

00:33:08.508 --> 00:33:10.135
Mine is just a clunker.

00:33:10.218 --> 00:33:12.262
Even Mr. Baek drives a domestic sedan.

00:33:12.345 --> 00:33:16.766
You won't have to change cars
until you make it to executive.

00:33:16.850 --> 00:33:19.144
Sir, please don't tease me.

00:33:19.978 --> 00:33:22.063
-How much was it?
-It was…

00:33:22.606 --> 00:33:24.399
That's Mr. Song's car.

00:33:25.025 --> 00:33:26.067
-Mr. Song.
-Ik-hyeon.

00:33:31.114 --> 00:33:33.408
-Ik-hyeon!
-Hello, Mr. Kim.

00:33:34.326 --> 00:33:36.995
Sung-gu. You finally bought it, huh?

00:33:38.204 --> 00:33:42.208
You've kept your car in great shape.

00:33:42.292 --> 00:33:44.628
So modest, so frugal,
and so pleasing to the eye.

00:33:44.711 --> 00:33:46.254
Yes.

00:33:46.338 --> 00:33:48.214
That car's just for commuting.

00:33:49.966 --> 00:33:51.635
Shall we head up now?

00:33:51.718 --> 00:33:53.428
We'll get ready for work.

00:33:57.932 --> 00:33:59.059
Ik-hyeon.

00:34:01.019 --> 00:34:02.646
Mr. Kim!

00:34:03.188 --> 00:34:05.148
You finally got a new bag!

00:34:05.231 --> 00:34:07.442
Mine was getting old, so I got a new one.

00:34:07.525 --> 00:34:10.362
It's the hottest designer brand.

00:34:10.445 --> 00:34:11.321
Mr. Do…

00:34:15.325 --> 00:34:16.576
Did you see Do Jin-woo's--

00:34:16.660 --> 00:34:18.536
Try again, Sung-gu.

00:34:19.621 --> 00:34:21.915
Did you buy it after seeing Jin-woo's bag?

00:34:22.415 --> 00:34:24.918
No. Does he have one too?

00:34:25.001 --> 00:34:25.877
Yes.

00:34:28.630 --> 00:34:30.256
-Ik-hyeon.
-Yes, sir.

00:34:30.340 --> 00:34:31.925
What do you drive on the weekends?

00:34:41.059 --> 00:34:43.311
Mr. Kim! Goodness. So heavy.

00:34:43.395 --> 00:34:45.105
What's so funny, guys?

00:34:45.188 --> 00:34:47.732
Myung-heon went on a blind date yesterday.

00:34:48.817 --> 00:34:50.026
Go on, tell him.

00:34:50.652 --> 00:34:52.737
-It wasn't bad.
-It sounds like it was.

00:34:52.821 --> 00:34:54.280
It was really bad.

00:34:54.364 --> 00:34:56.199
As a woman, I think it's a lost cause.

00:34:56.282 --> 00:34:57.826
She was nice enough,

00:34:57.909 --> 00:35:00.412
but she wouldn't pay a dime
until the third round.

00:35:02.372 --> 00:35:03.456
And?

00:35:14.592 --> 00:35:17.095
That's the one the clerk
recommended yesterday.

00:35:17.178 --> 00:35:19.597
With the credit card discount,
it comes to 2.3 million…

00:35:19.681 --> 00:35:21.975
It's 2.3 million won.

00:35:22.767 --> 00:35:23.810
I won.

00:35:24.352 --> 00:35:26.229
-I won!
-Is that so?

00:35:30.817 --> 00:35:32.110
Cheer up.

00:35:32.193 --> 00:35:33.278
We can do it!

00:35:34.738 --> 00:35:35.739
We can do it!

00:35:36.448 --> 00:35:38.450
-Drink up!
-Bottoms up!

00:35:38.533 --> 00:35:39.826
-Here.
-Long time no see.

00:35:39.909 --> 00:35:41.035
Go get your hair dyed.

00:35:41.119 --> 00:35:43.288
Chip in some money before you say that.

00:35:44.998 --> 00:35:47.292
So, are you making executive
this year or what?

00:35:47.375 --> 00:35:49.878
I've got a rival on the other team,
but he's not a threat.

00:35:49.961 --> 00:35:52.130
No connections,
and just a junior college grad.

00:35:52.213 --> 00:35:54.716
Isn't he on the same sales team as you?

00:35:55.216 --> 00:35:56.468
Why do you ask?

00:35:56.551 --> 00:35:59.846
I think I saw him
on your company's YouTube channel.

00:35:59.929 --> 00:36:01.222
-Hang on.
-What is it?

00:36:01.306 --> 00:36:02.348
I'm Do Jin-woo,

00:36:02.432 --> 00:36:03.892
-general manager…
-Watch.

00:36:03.975 --> 00:36:06.311
-It's him, right?
-… of Sales Team 2 at ACT.

00:36:06.394 --> 00:36:08.271
-Mr. Do! Hang on.
-That punk.

00:36:08.354 --> 00:36:10.231
-It's him.
-You're a general manager?

00:36:10.315 --> 00:36:12.484
Why would you look up a video like this?

00:36:12.567 --> 00:36:15.153
We watch stuff like this all day at PR.

00:36:15.236 --> 00:36:16.488
How old is he?

00:36:16.571 --> 00:36:17.947
He looks young.

00:36:18.031 --> 00:36:20.200
-I don't know.
-To be a general manager at his age,

00:36:20.283 --> 00:36:22.160
he must've had fast-track promotions.

00:36:22.243 --> 00:36:23.995
Did they ask you
to film something like this?

00:36:24.078 --> 00:36:25.413
Whatever.

00:36:25.497 --> 00:36:27.791
They didn't, did they?

00:36:27.874 --> 00:36:29.167
They didn't.

00:36:29.250 --> 00:36:30.877
If I were the boss,

00:36:30.960 --> 00:36:32.837
I'd make him the managing director. Look.

00:36:32.921 --> 00:36:35.298
-Get that out of my face.
-Stay still.

00:36:35.381 --> 00:36:38.426
You see, these days, even executives
have to be young and good-looking.

00:36:38.510 --> 00:36:41.095
How does putting up an old man like you
help the company's image?

00:36:41.179 --> 00:36:43.014
Get it out of my face!

00:36:43.097 --> 00:36:44.724
Shouldn't you start

00:36:44.808 --> 00:36:46.351
going to startup fairs like me?

00:36:46.434 --> 00:36:47.852
Don't talk crap.

00:36:47.936 --> 00:36:50.480
Say what you will,
but I'm the number one choice.

00:36:50.563 --> 00:36:52.023
He went to a junior college.

00:36:52.106 --> 00:36:55.318
You moron.
Can't you see the bigger picture?

00:36:55.401 --> 00:36:57.111
Once you've made it to general manager,

00:36:57.195 --> 00:37:00.990
a junior college degree
isn't a handicap. It's a weapon.

00:37:01.074 --> 00:37:03.827
It's a testament to 100% pure skill.

00:37:03.910 --> 00:37:06.830
Isn't your company always
talking about ESG management?

00:37:06.913 --> 00:37:09.415
An executive in his forties
from a junior college

00:37:10.083 --> 00:37:12.627
would be perfect for refreshing
the company's image.

00:37:12.710 --> 00:37:14.587
-That's so true.
-The usual for me!

00:37:14.671 --> 00:37:15.922
All right.

00:37:16.005 --> 00:37:18.216
-Here!
-Sorry, I'm late!

00:37:18.299 --> 00:37:19.843
-Gosh.
-I'm so sorry!

00:37:19.926 --> 00:37:22.345
How is the jobless one
always the last to arrive?

00:37:22.428 --> 00:37:23.388
My apologies! Sorry!

00:37:23.471 --> 00:37:26.099
A tenant suddenly decided to move out,
so I'm all over the place.

00:37:26.182 --> 00:37:28.268
-The third floor?
-They had the whole floor.

00:37:28.351 --> 00:37:29.519
Was it the cram school?

00:37:29.602 --> 00:37:32.939
Yes. I thought they'd stay for a while.

00:37:33.022 --> 00:37:35.066
It's hard to rent out
the third and fourth floors.

00:37:35.149 --> 00:37:37.193
-That's right.
-What are you talking about?

00:37:37.277 --> 00:37:39.904
-It's about the building.
-What building?

00:37:40.947 --> 00:37:42.282
I told you.

00:37:42.365 --> 00:37:44.784
I bought an eight-story building
at the end of last year.

00:37:44.868 --> 00:37:46.077
Who did?

00:37:46.160 --> 00:37:47.078
I did!

00:37:48.663 --> 00:37:50.707
-What?
-They call me a landlord.

00:37:50.790 --> 00:37:52.667
But I'm basically their call center.

00:37:52.750 --> 00:37:54.168
The moment something goes wrong,

00:37:54.252 --> 00:37:56.713
they call me night and day.

00:37:57.714 --> 00:37:58.965
I'm so over it.

00:37:59.465 --> 00:38:00.925
Have some food.

00:38:01.009 --> 00:38:02.135
You bought a building?

00:38:03.136 --> 00:38:04.137
You punk.

00:38:04.637 --> 00:38:06.556
You don't read the group chat, do you?

00:38:06.639 --> 00:38:09.100
Didn't you know?
He only reads it when it's about him.

00:38:09.183 --> 00:38:11.060
-Come on.
-You all knew about this?

00:38:11.144 --> 00:38:12.061
Jeez.

00:38:12.729 --> 00:38:15.398
-The usual.
-Thank you.

00:38:18.943 --> 00:38:21.404
-How much is the rent?
-I get around 30 million won.

00:38:23.740 --> 00:38:26.117
I didn't mean the yearly rent, stupid.
This isn't Jeju Island.

00:38:26.200 --> 00:38:28.995
I know! I meant the monthly rent!

00:38:29.078 --> 00:38:30.747
I get 30 million won per month.

00:38:32.957 --> 00:38:35.251
Hey, this one's good.

00:38:35.335 --> 00:38:38.588
30 MILLION WON PER MONTH

00:38:41.299 --> 00:38:42.508
I'm so damn jealous.

00:38:44.135 --> 00:38:46.054
Don't be jealous, Nak-su.

00:38:46.137 --> 00:38:47.972
Half of it ends up in taxes.

00:38:48.056 --> 00:38:50.558
I pay three million won
just for health insurance.

00:38:51.517 --> 00:38:54.729
Once you make executive next year,
that'll all be chump change for you.

00:38:54.812 --> 00:38:56.898
You'll become one next year, right?

00:39:00.276 --> 00:39:02.320
-What's so funny?
-Will he not?

00:39:02.403 --> 00:39:03.363
It's nothing.

00:39:05.137 --> 00:39:06.282
Come on. Bottoms up.

00:39:06.574 --> 00:39:07.450
TAE-HWAN

00:39:07.533 --> 00:39:08.701
It's good.

00:39:08.785 --> 00:39:09.702
No.

00:39:09.786 --> 00:39:12.163
-Stop pouring.
-I'm drinking too.

00:39:16.417 --> 00:39:18.920
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable.

00:39:19.003 --> 00:39:19.963
Please leave a message…

00:39:20.046 --> 00:39:21.214
NAK-SU

00:39:34.519 --> 00:39:36.688
BEYOND TELECOMMUNICATION
CONNECTING PEOPLE

00:39:36.771 --> 00:39:37.897
WE CONNECT THE FUTURE

00:40:33.161 --> 00:40:34.454
JEALOUSY, MY STRENGTH

00:40:51.512 --> 00:40:54.682
Hello, I'm Lee Jeong-hwan,
the CEO of Jealousy, My Strength.

00:40:59.812 --> 00:41:02.899
The journey to this moment
has been full of hardships,

00:41:02.982 --> 00:41:05.610
and I'm deeply grateful
to the many people who stood by me

00:41:05.693 --> 00:41:07.612
and helped me overcome them.

00:41:07.695 --> 00:41:11.574
I'd especially like to thank
those who decided to invest in us.

00:41:11.657 --> 00:41:13.242
This is more than just funding.

00:41:13.326 --> 00:41:16.996
It's an acknowledgment of the vision
of Jealousy, My Strength.

00:41:22.251 --> 00:41:23.711
I've been looking for you.

00:41:23.795 --> 00:41:25.963
Answer your phone, will you?

00:41:26.047 --> 00:41:27.799
-We'll talk details later.
-Okay.

00:41:27.882 --> 00:41:29.425
-The night is young.
-Sorry.

00:41:42.605 --> 00:41:45.149
-Jeong-hwan! Over here!
-Hi.

00:41:48.945 --> 00:41:50.029
How did I do?

00:41:50.113 --> 00:41:51.489
You did great.

00:41:51.572 --> 00:41:53.449
Let's finish our conversation.

00:41:57.703 --> 00:42:00.706
A clothing company makes clothes.
A film company makes films.

00:42:00.790 --> 00:42:02.333
Those days are now over.

00:42:02.416 --> 00:42:04.252
The brand itself.

00:42:04.335 --> 00:42:06.254
Setting up a solid brand.

00:42:06.337 --> 00:42:08.214
That's where I'm going to start.

00:42:08.297 --> 00:42:10.758
A loyal customer base
will naturally follow.

00:42:10.842 --> 00:42:13.469
People who would gladly open their wallets

00:42:13.553 --> 00:42:16.597
even if we were to make
fire extinguishers or gas masks.

00:42:17.390 --> 00:42:18.975
Can I ask a question?

00:42:21.477 --> 00:42:23.229
Can you tell me your name first?

00:42:23.312 --> 00:42:24.397
Kim Su-gyeom.

00:42:30.361 --> 00:42:33.531
So at the end of the day,
what kind of company is this?

00:42:34.240 --> 00:42:35.116
What?

00:42:36.075 --> 00:42:37.994
He just explained it.

00:42:39.453 --> 00:42:43.583
Even after all that,
I still don't quite follow.

00:42:44.458 --> 00:42:46.586
Are you saying
you'll actually make gas masks?

00:42:46.669 --> 00:42:49.922
What exactly is it that you'll do?
How are you going to make money?

00:42:50.006 --> 00:42:51.924
Was it

00:42:52.675 --> 00:42:55.011
some kind of metaphor? Gas masks?

00:42:55.094 --> 00:42:56.846
Am I missing something here?

00:43:10.735 --> 00:43:12.945
I'm asking because I want to see
if my gut's right.

00:43:13.029 --> 00:43:14.155
Your parents are…

00:43:14.822 --> 00:43:17.283
that is to say, your mother
is probably a homemaker,

00:43:17.366 --> 00:43:19.118
and your father's an office worker, right?

00:43:19.202 --> 00:43:20.119
Yes.

00:43:20.745 --> 00:43:23.331
Your major is
either business or economics,

00:43:23.414 --> 00:43:25.166
and you're Korean, right?

00:43:25.249 --> 00:43:26.125
Sorry?

00:43:26.209 --> 00:43:28.586
You live in Seoul
in a house owned by your parents.

00:43:28.669 --> 00:43:29.587
Yes.

00:43:30.254 --> 00:43:32.173
Do you live in Gangnam or Seocho?

00:43:33.174 --> 00:43:34.175
No.

00:43:34.258 --> 00:43:36.010
Okay, I was right 100%.

00:43:36.969 --> 00:43:38.512
I knew you'd like him.

00:43:40.640 --> 00:43:43.059
You don't act like you're
from Gangnam or Seocho.

00:43:52.485 --> 00:43:54.695
We just met. Why talk down to me?

00:44:04.455 --> 00:44:06.666
100,000 won feels trivial now.

00:44:06.749 --> 00:44:08.084
But in 20, 30 years,

00:44:08.167 --> 00:44:10.878
it could be the difference
between life and death.

00:44:10.962 --> 00:44:13.589
Make sure you save the money and--

00:44:16.425 --> 00:44:17.551
Hello.

00:44:18.511 --> 00:44:20.137
Did you buy a new bag?

00:44:20.221 --> 00:44:21.555
No, it was a gift.

00:44:22.181 --> 00:44:24.892
-Is there anything to snack on?
-You're going to keep drinking?

00:44:24.976 --> 00:44:27.770
Just give me whatever.
Anchovies and beans will do.

00:44:27.853 --> 00:44:30.731
You said Loafer bought something.
Is it making him some money?

00:44:30.815 --> 00:44:32.400
I don't know.

00:44:34.694 --> 00:44:36.570
"Avoid a miserable retirement"?

00:44:37.321 --> 00:44:40.199
It's nothing. It just came up.

00:44:40.283 --> 00:44:42.201
-Park Ha-jin.
-What?

00:44:42.285 --> 00:44:44.287
Don't underestimate your husband.

00:44:44.370 --> 00:44:46.539
What do you mean?

00:44:46.622 --> 00:44:48.582
I really am going to become
an executive next year.

00:44:48.666 --> 00:44:51.294
Goodness. Okay, I got it.

00:44:51.377 --> 00:44:53.004
Go get changed.

00:44:53.087 --> 00:44:55.131
What's going on?

00:44:55.214 --> 00:44:57.675
I said I wouldn't make you work.
Why are you watching that?

00:44:57.758 --> 00:44:59.593
Okay, I got it. Go on.

00:44:59.677 --> 00:45:02.179
Goodness, you stink. You should go change.

00:45:11.897 --> 00:45:13.399
That punk.

00:45:16.319 --> 00:45:18.487
My son is home!

00:45:21.240 --> 00:45:23.075
Welcome home, Su-gyeom.

00:45:23.159 --> 00:45:25.119
-I'm home.
-Oh my.

00:45:25.202 --> 00:45:26.412
Su-gyeom, you're home.

00:45:26.495 --> 00:45:27.872
Did you have dinner?

00:45:28.789 --> 00:45:30.541
Come and have a drink with me.

00:45:30.624 --> 00:45:31.917
A drink?

00:45:32.001 --> 00:45:34.086
-Goodness.
-Sit down.

00:45:34.170 --> 00:45:35.379
Sit.

00:45:36.130 --> 00:45:39.175
-You two have a good time.
-Dad, I'm…

00:45:43.095 --> 00:45:44.638
Want to try the CSAT a third time?

00:45:44.722 --> 00:45:45.890
No.

00:45:50.770 --> 00:45:52.229
Do you want to study abroad?

00:45:53.647 --> 00:45:55.024
Why are you doing this to me?

00:45:55.107 --> 00:45:56.067
What do you mean?

00:45:57.610 --> 00:45:59.779
Tell me if you want to do it, okay?

00:46:00.988 --> 00:46:03.741
People say academic background
doesn't mean anything.

00:46:03.824 --> 00:46:06.494
But things are different
once you step out into the real world.

00:46:06.577 --> 00:46:07.578
Dad,

00:46:07.661 --> 00:46:10.956
I have class early in the morning.
I'm gonna call it a night.

00:46:11.040 --> 00:46:13.542
I need to go to the office early too.

00:46:13.626 --> 00:46:14.960
Sit down.

00:46:15.711 --> 00:46:17.004
Let's talk.

00:46:18.506 --> 00:46:20.716
-Here.
-Okay.

00:46:26.347 --> 00:46:27.223
Son.

00:46:28.641 --> 00:46:32.853
One of my friends is a landlord.

00:46:33.646 --> 00:46:37.858
He owns an eight-story building.
It's huge.

00:46:38.484 --> 00:46:40.486
Do you know how much he makes from rent?

00:46:41.278 --> 00:46:43.614
He gets 30 million won.

00:46:43.697 --> 00:46:44.949
Jeez.

00:46:46.283 --> 00:46:48.786
Goodness gracious. I'm super jealous.

00:46:49.537 --> 00:46:50.454
No.

00:46:51.122 --> 00:46:53.916
You think I'd be jealous of him?

00:46:53.999 --> 00:46:54.917
Not at all.

00:46:55.626 --> 00:46:57.711
I'm not jealous at all.

00:46:58.421 --> 00:46:59.672
Do you know why?

00:46:59.755 --> 00:47:02.133
Because he's still a jobless bum.

00:47:03.843 --> 00:47:06.345
Owning a building means
he's in the rental business.

00:47:06.429 --> 00:47:08.639
-How is he a jobless bum?
-He is.

00:47:08.722 --> 00:47:12.059
He lives on unearned income.
What else could he be?

00:47:12.143 --> 00:47:14.103
Why is that unearned income?

00:47:14.186 --> 00:47:18.190
A landlord has to manage the place,
deal with complaints and whatnot.

00:47:19.108 --> 00:47:22.486
You think people are jealous of landlords
just because they're rich?

00:47:22.570 --> 00:47:25.197
People mock them behind their backs.

00:47:25.281 --> 00:47:27.283
You think a guy
dragging his slippers around

00:47:27.366 --> 00:47:29.118
will get any respect from society?

00:47:30.369 --> 00:47:31.996
How would you know that?

00:47:32.872 --> 00:47:33.831
Of course I know!

00:47:33.914 --> 00:47:36.917
I'm over 50. You think I don't know that?

00:47:37.001 --> 00:47:38.002
I know everything.

00:47:42.923 --> 00:47:45.342
The same goes for my older brother.

00:47:45.426 --> 00:47:47.761
He acted all high and mighty,

00:47:47.845 --> 00:47:51.348
but he got left behind
and now runs a car repair shop.

00:47:51.432 --> 00:47:53.017
You saw him last holiday.

00:47:53.100 --> 00:47:56.020
All that grease on his face and clothes.

00:47:56.103 --> 00:47:57.897
-Gosh.
-What's wrong with that?

00:47:58.856 --> 00:48:01.692
I'm not saying it's wrong.

00:48:02.693 --> 00:48:05.070
What I want to say

00:48:06.822 --> 00:48:09.074
is that in Korea, after all,

00:48:09.700 --> 00:48:13.329
you've got to land a job
at a leading global corporation,

00:48:13.412 --> 00:48:16.081
sit at a desk,

00:48:16.165 --> 00:48:19.376
and type away to make money.

00:48:20.044 --> 00:48:22.129
This is both the standard

00:48:22.838 --> 00:48:26.050
and the most ideal outcome.

00:48:26.133 --> 00:48:27.468
Understood?

00:48:32.181 --> 00:48:34.141
I seem very average to you, don't I?

00:48:36.101 --> 00:48:38.938
But do you have any idea
how hard it is to lead an average life?

00:48:41.357 --> 00:48:44.818
You won't get it
until you step into the real world.

00:48:45.736 --> 00:48:46.654
Do you understand?

00:48:48.447 --> 00:48:49.532
I respect you, Dad.

00:48:49.615 --> 00:48:51.492
I know you've achieved a lot, but--

00:48:57.623 --> 00:48:59.375
You have no idea.

00:49:01.293 --> 00:49:03.963
If you did,
you wouldn't talk to me like that.

00:49:09.218 --> 00:49:10.302
Son.

00:49:11.262 --> 00:49:12.805
-Yes.
-My son.

00:49:12.888 --> 00:49:14.014
Yes.

00:49:15.975 --> 00:49:17.268
Remember this.

00:49:19.228 --> 00:49:22.398
Surviving 25 years at a major corporation
as a general manager,

00:49:24.567 --> 00:49:26.068
buying an apartment in Seoul,

00:49:28.070 --> 00:49:29.947
and sending a kid to college…

00:49:31.699 --> 00:49:32.992
That's greatness.

00:49:37.663 --> 00:49:39.123
That's greatness, kiddo.

00:49:56.432 --> 00:49:57.516
Su-gyeom.

00:49:58.017 --> 00:50:01.353
Go to your room. I'll take care of him.
Go get some sleep.

00:50:02.605 --> 00:50:04.064
You've got class tomorrow. Go on.

00:50:09.111 --> 00:50:10.029
Honey.

00:50:11.113 --> 00:50:11.989
Honey.

00:50:12.489 --> 00:50:14.575
Let's get you to the bedroom. Come.

00:50:14.658 --> 00:50:17.202
Come on. Let's get you to bed.

00:50:42.686 --> 00:50:45.397
I just want to be somebody.

00:51:00.204 --> 00:51:03.415
It's a bull market.

00:51:03.499 --> 00:51:04.750
Great.

00:51:08.921 --> 00:51:10.047
"Jin-woo"

00:51:10.130 --> 00:51:12.299
GENERAL MANAGER DO JIN-WOO

00:51:12.383 --> 00:51:13.717
"Can I have your address?"

00:51:16.762 --> 00:51:18.222
"I want to pick you up,

00:51:19.264 --> 00:51:20.516
but I need the address."

00:51:21.016 --> 00:51:22.601
This punk.

00:51:22.685 --> 00:51:25.396
He should have sent it already.
So much for seniority.

00:51:30.484 --> 00:51:32.986
I'm sorry, Mr. Kim. I was too busy.

00:51:33.070 --> 00:51:34.196
It's Building 201.

00:51:35.739 --> 00:51:36.615
Jeez.

00:51:36.699 --> 00:51:37.574
YOUR FULL ADDRESS

00:51:37.658 --> 00:51:40.786
It's right across from Mr. Baek's place.
It could be confusing.

00:51:42.996 --> 00:51:45.958
You may find it more convenient to type
"Banpo River Palace Building 201"

00:51:46.041 --> 00:51:47.209
into the GPS.

00:51:51.880 --> 00:51:53.173
Good morning.

00:51:53.257 --> 00:51:55.134
I'm on my way.

00:51:55.217 --> 00:51:57.511
Hi, Nak-su. Come to think of it,

00:51:57.594 --> 00:52:00.222
I realized I left my golf bag
in Jin-woo's car.

00:52:00.723 --> 00:52:03.350
I'll just walk to his place.
See you there.

00:52:03.851 --> 00:52:06.854
Okay. I'll be there.

00:52:13.819 --> 00:52:17.614
BANPO BRIDGE
WELCOME TO SEOCHO

00:52:21.910 --> 00:52:23.746
"Palace," my foot.

00:52:23.829 --> 00:52:26.290
What are they? Royalty living in a palace?

00:52:40.095 --> 00:52:42.139
Jin-woo is so young, though. Jeez.

00:52:43.265 --> 00:52:44.933
I bet he's on a key money lease.

00:52:45.768 --> 00:52:48.020
Please be on a key money system.

00:52:48.103 --> 00:52:49.605
He has to be.

00:53:01.658 --> 00:53:03.285
How much is the key money lease?

00:53:04.369 --> 00:53:08.749
Key money for River Palace.

00:53:09.958 --> 00:53:11.084
3.8 BILLION
3.7 BILLION

00:53:13.170 --> 00:53:14.379
How can it be?

00:53:17.382 --> 00:53:19.384
Can you open the trunk, please?

00:53:20.385 --> 00:53:21.637
Sure.

00:53:24.056 --> 00:53:25.766
I've been going crazy these days.

00:53:25.849 --> 00:53:29.102
Looks like there's an issue
with your address position.

00:53:29.186 --> 00:53:30.103
Is that so?

00:53:30.187 --> 00:53:32.731
If your right arm is bent,
your backswing can be too fast,

00:53:32.815 --> 00:53:34.358
and you're more likely to slice.

00:53:34.441 --> 00:53:36.109
Darn it.

00:53:36.193 --> 00:53:38.278
I should have shown it to you sooner.

00:53:39.321 --> 00:53:40.572
Gosh, so much traffic.

00:53:40.656 --> 00:53:42.783
Sorry, Nak-su.
I'll hop into the front seat in a minute.

00:53:42.866 --> 00:53:45.536
Don't worry.
Whatever feels comfortable for you.

00:53:45.619 --> 00:53:48.038
The back seat is so spacious.

00:53:48.121 --> 00:53:49.581
Right?

00:53:49.665 --> 00:53:51.166
I'd love a big car like this.

00:53:51.959 --> 00:53:53.544
Okay. My right arm.

00:53:53.627 --> 00:53:55.295
-Mr. Baek.
-Yes.

00:53:55.921 --> 00:53:59.049
How's the new apartment?

00:53:59.716 --> 00:54:02.052
I'm only renting here monthly,
so it's temporary.

00:54:03.053 --> 00:54:05.264
You bought early
and pocketed some cash, huh?

00:54:05.347 --> 00:54:06.515
-Hardly.
-What?

00:54:06.598 --> 00:54:08.600
The price's gone up a bit
since I bought it.

00:54:09.309 --> 00:54:10.686
-Here.
-My right arm?

00:54:10.769 --> 00:54:13.021
-Yes, your right arm.
-He owns it!

00:54:14.231 --> 00:54:16.024
Why are you gaping like that?

00:54:20.904 --> 00:54:22.155
Shall I drive?

00:54:23.031 --> 00:54:24.324
-Can you…
-Shall I?

00:54:24.408 --> 00:54:25.325
Thank you.

00:54:26.493 --> 00:54:29.913
You get a turn, and I get a turn.
It sounds sweet,

00:54:29.997 --> 00:54:32.457
but it's also perfect
for drawing unnecessary suspicion.

00:54:32.541 --> 00:54:33.417
RIVER PALACE PRICES

00:54:33.500 --> 00:54:34.668
Jeez, come on.

00:54:34.751 --> 00:54:37.504
Don't be so pessimistic.

00:54:37.588 --> 00:54:40.632
If you think about the bidding price,
it's a risk worth taking.

00:54:40.716 --> 00:54:41.842
6.8 BILLION
6.7 BILLION

00:54:41.925 --> 00:54:43.886
I'm not sure.

00:54:47.180 --> 00:54:50.309
Going with a separate contract structure…

00:54:50.976 --> 00:54:52.519
Did he come just to play around?

00:54:53.437 --> 00:54:56.148
ACT won't be the only one
who will benefit from it.

00:54:56.231 --> 00:54:57.608
Nak-su!

00:54:57.691 --> 00:54:58.817
What are you doing? Come!

00:54:58.901 --> 00:55:00.193
Yes, sir.

00:55:01.278 --> 00:55:02.362
KIM NAK-SU

00:55:15.709 --> 00:55:19.296
I always crush him
whenever we bet on golf.

00:55:19.796 --> 00:55:21.673
He's a total sucker.

00:55:22.174 --> 00:55:23.926
Still, his form's actually pretty solid.

00:55:24.676 --> 00:55:25.886
-You think?
-Yes. Look at him.

00:55:25.969 --> 00:55:28.263
He's not using any unnecessary force.

00:55:29.097 --> 00:55:30.515
He must have inherited it.

00:55:31.058 --> 00:55:33.393
Maybe not. Sneaky bastard.

00:55:33.477 --> 00:55:36.521
Acting all honorable,
acting like he's not into investments.

00:55:36.605 --> 00:55:37.522
What a phony bastard.

00:55:37.606 --> 00:55:39.149
Just wait. I'll get there.

00:55:40.359 --> 00:55:41.360
I'll get there.

00:55:41.443 --> 00:55:44.613
I'll become an executive

00:55:45.238 --> 00:55:48.200
and make my way
to Gangnam, Seocho, and Hannam.

00:55:48.283 --> 00:55:49.701
Good shot.

00:56:03.548 --> 00:56:04.716
It went in.

00:56:04.800 --> 00:56:06.510
-Hole-in-one!
-It went in!

00:56:08.261 --> 00:56:09.638
-What the heck?
-A hole-in-one?

00:56:09.721 --> 00:56:10.889
-Hey!
-Oh my.

00:56:10.973 --> 00:56:12.724
It's a hole-in-one!

00:56:14.601 --> 00:56:16.353
That's a hole-in-one!

00:56:16.895 --> 00:56:18.313
Mr. Baek!

00:56:20.107 --> 00:56:21.608
I can't believe that went in.

00:56:21.692 --> 00:56:25.070
It's been 15 years, but I've never
claimed my hole-in-one insurance.

00:56:25.153 --> 00:56:26.738
You've got coverage, right?

00:56:26.822 --> 00:56:28.615
No, I don't.

00:56:28.699 --> 00:56:29.950
Not even one-day coverage?

00:56:30.033 --> 00:56:31.034
No.

00:56:36.206 --> 00:56:37.791
KIM NAK-SU

00:56:37.874 --> 00:56:39.209
I mean, nothing's impossible.

00:56:39.292 --> 00:56:40.293
CONGRATULATIONS
HOLE-IN-ONE

00:56:40.377 --> 00:56:42.004
Mr. Hole-in-One, stand in the center.

00:56:42.087 --> 00:56:43.588
-Come to the center.
-I'm good.

00:56:43.672 --> 00:56:45.048
Come on.

00:56:45.132 --> 00:56:47.175
-The star of the day.
-Closer, please.

00:56:47.259 --> 00:56:48.427
Here we go.

00:56:48.510 --> 00:56:50.679
One, two, three.

00:56:50.762 --> 00:56:53.015
Good! Let's see some bigger smiles.

00:56:59.855 --> 00:57:02.566
DREAM BANK

00:57:02.649 --> 00:57:04.151
Thank you for today.

00:57:04.234 --> 00:57:06.278
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

00:57:06.361 --> 00:57:08.238
-Right. And sir?
-Yes.

00:57:08.321 --> 00:57:10.198
You're getting
the commemorative ball, right?

00:57:10.282 --> 00:57:11.199
A commemorative ball?

00:57:11.283 --> 00:57:13.076
This is a real good-luck charm.

00:57:13.160 --> 00:57:14.286
Everyone buys one.

00:57:17.247 --> 00:57:18.290
Sure.

00:57:18.373 --> 00:57:20.792
-Go for it all.
-I'll ring it up for you.

00:57:32.345 --> 00:57:33.430
There.

00:57:33.513 --> 00:57:35.932
This is where it gets really amazing.

00:57:36.016 --> 00:57:38.727
This one's called the Nak-su Bomb!

00:57:38.810 --> 00:57:40.145
Down it goes!

00:57:43.231 --> 00:57:44.858
Pour it all in.

00:57:44.941 --> 00:57:46.943
-All right.
-What?

00:57:47.027 --> 00:57:49.988
The last par!

00:57:52.240 --> 00:57:54.701
We are no longer competitors.

00:57:54.785 --> 00:57:56.495
We're partners!

00:57:56.578 --> 00:57:58.747
Let's love each other!

00:57:58.830 --> 00:58:00.540
-Love each other!
-Love each other!

00:58:04.711 --> 00:58:06.213
Let's order some more meat.

00:58:06.296 --> 00:58:08.256
-Shall we?
-Eight more servings!

00:58:08.340 --> 00:58:09.716
That will be 2,490,000 won.

00:58:10.550 --> 00:58:11.968
Sorry?

00:58:12.052 --> 00:58:13.512
It's 2,490,000 won.

00:58:14.387 --> 00:58:15.806
Right.

00:58:15.889 --> 00:58:17.599
Shall I chip in?

00:58:17.682 --> 00:58:19.392
Goodness. Just go already.

00:58:19.476 --> 00:58:20.352
-Take him.
-Okay.

00:58:20.435 --> 00:58:22.229
I'll pay in full.

00:58:22.312 --> 00:58:23.188
Here.

00:58:24.022 --> 00:58:25.315
In full.

00:58:26.608 --> 00:58:27.901
What do I do now?

00:58:27.984 --> 00:58:28.860
RECEIPT

00:58:33.782 --> 00:58:35.283
Mr. Baek.

00:58:39.412 --> 00:58:41.081
Holy cow!

00:58:42.332 --> 00:58:43.667
Be careful.

00:58:43.750 --> 00:58:45.585
-Is this pure gold?
-I paid 1.5 million won.

00:58:46.711 --> 00:58:48.755
We should have bought it for you.

00:58:48.839 --> 00:58:49.965
Please. That's not necessary.

00:58:50.048 --> 00:58:52.634
You did a good job.

00:58:52.717 --> 00:58:55.303
You need to pay good money
for something like this.

00:58:55.387 --> 00:58:56.763
That was no ordinary luck.

00:58:56.847 --> 00:58:58.807
That was a stroke of great fortune!

00:59:00.100 --> 00:59:01.768
My number one treasure,

00:59:01.852 --> 00:59:03.478
Kim Nak-su!

00:59:04.813 --> 00:59:06.273
The managing director.

00:59:07.482 --> 00:59:08.859
Thank you.

00:59:08.942 --> 00:59:10.235
Okay.

00:59:13.446 --> 00:59:15.532
Let's have coffee in my office
this afternoon.

00:59:15.615 --> 00:59:16.658
Okay.

00:59:18.743 --> 00:59:21.204
Your boss scored a hole-in-one.

00:59:21.288 --> 00:59:22.664
Take good care of him.

00:59:24.708 --> 00:59:27.419
You know how crucial this is, right?

00:59:29.254 --> 00:59:31.047
Let's have a successful
first half of the year.

00:59:31.131 --> 00:59:33.175
Numbers make the man.

00:59:33.258 --> 00:59:34.217
Yes, sir.

00:59:38.680 --> 00:59:39.681
Bye, sir.

00:59:42.309 --> 00:59:43.977
-Bye, sir.
-All right.

00:59:44.060 --> 00:59:47.147
Mr. Kim, I did the final check,
and there's something ambiguous.

00:59:47.230 --> 00:59:48.148
Ambiguous?

00:59:48.231 --> 00:59:50.275
The estimate for
the Yangpyeong Dream Cultural Center

00:59:50.358 --> 00:59:53.236
is a bit ambiguous,
so I'd like for you to take a look.

00:59:55.363 --> 00:59:56.323
What's ambiguous?

00:59:56.406 --> 00:59:59.242
The quote was based on Super Giga,

00:59:59.326 --> 01:00:01.953
but this area isn't covered yet.

01:00:06.708 --> 01:00:08.293
CONSTRUCTION MAP
SCHEDULED FOR AUGUST 2025

01:00:08.376 --> 01:00:10.921
That's not true. They're getting
Giga Internet starting in August.

01:00:11.004 --> 01:00:13.715
Yes, but we have to start
the service next week.

01:00:14.758 --> 01:00:16.760
What? Is there a problem?

01:00:16.843 --> 01:00:18.762
No, sir.

01:00:19.721 --> 01:00:20.805
What's there to worry about?

01:00:22.265 --> 01:00:24.893
Get it installed.
It's just a few months at most.

01:00:24.976 --> 01:00:26.770
-No need to hesitate. Come on.
-Okay.

01:00:28.438 --> 01:00:29.564
Come see me around 2:00 p.m.

01:00:29.648 --> 01:00:30.607
I will.

01:00:32.609 --> 01:00:34.069
-Bye, sir.
-Bye, sir.

01:00:38.698 --> 01:00:39.616
Hey.

01:00:40.575 --> 01:00:43.245
They won't be doing
any speed checks or anything,

01:00:43.328 --> 01:00:45.997
but make sure nothing goes wrong, okay?

01:00:46.915 --> 01:00:49.542
-You know what I mean, right?
-Yes, sir.

01:00:49.626 --> 01:00:51.211
-Hello.
-Long time no see.

01:01:02.681 --> 01:01:04.099
Hello.

01:01:04.182 --> 01:01:05.141
It's been a while.

01:01:06.768 --> 01:01:07.894
What brings you here?

01:01:11.189 --> 01:01:13.692
I just…

01:01:17.320 --> 01:01:19.155
Have you eaten?

01:01:20.156 --> 01:01:21.241
No.

01:01:22.409 --> 01:01:24.703
Let's go. Give me a second.

01:01:31.376 --> 01:01:32.627
Is there absolutely no way?

01:01:34.587 --> 01:01:37.257
I guess I can arrange
a meeting over a meal.

01:01:37.340 --> 01:01:40.051
That's more than enough.
I'll take care of the rest.

01:01:42.679 --> 01:01:44.889
The HR team already made the call.

01:01:44.973 --> 01:01:47.434
I don't see how Jeong-tae
can get you out of this.

01:01:49.102 --> 01:01:50.645
Still, I need to try.

01:01:56.401 --> 01:01:57.610
Nak-su, I…

01:01:59.070 --> 01:02:02.157
I go up and down those manholes
dozens of times a day,

01:02:04.242 --> 01:02:05.702
opening and closing the lids.

01:02:08.371 --> 01:02:09.998
But it's so dark down there.

01:02:12.917 --> 01:02:15.253
I really feel
like I'm going to die, Nak-su.

01:02:17.380 --> 01:02:19.591
I bet those bastards

01:02:20.759 --> 01:02:23.428
never planned on sending me
to Ulleungdo in the first place.

01:02:23.511 --> 01:02:26.473
Looking at it now, they just want me
to quit on my own.

01:02:26.556 --> 01:02:27.891
Buddy.

01:02:29.351 --> 01:02:31.311
Did you only just figure that out?

01:02:32.020 --> 01:02:34.189
-What?
-I'll be straight with you.

01:02:34.272 --> 01:02:37.484
I feel embarrassed
about having to go to Jeong-tae and say,

01:02:37.567 --> 01:02:40.653
"My buddy's about to get demoted.
Could you please look out for him?"

01:02:40.737 --> 01:02:42.447
At a time like this,

01:02:42.530 --> 01:02:45.617
I don't want to sound
like I'm oblivious to reality.

01:02:46.534 --> 01:02:47.744
I'm desperate too.

01:02:47.827 --> 01:02:50.455
I've been a general manager for six years.
This is my last year.

01:02:50.538 --> 01:02:54.167
You think I don't notice how the company
pampers that kid, Do Jin-woo?

01:02:56.669 --> 01:02:58.505
But we're colleagues.

01:02:59.089 --> 01:03:00.965
We came in together, Nak-su.

01:03:01.049 --> 01:03:03.426
Stop making that face. I'm so sick of it.

01:03:05.553 --> 01:03:06.971
Stop acting like you're the victim.

01:03:07.055 --> 01:03:08.890
I'm the victim, not you.

01:03:21.319 --> 01:03:23.655
-Song-hee.
-Yes, sir.

01:03:46.219 --> 01:03:48.847
-Here.
-Thank you.

01:03:54.102 --> 01:03:56.521
I know you're up for a promotion

01:03:57.230 --> 01:03:59.190
to assistant manager next year,

01:04:00.108 --> 01:04:01.234
but…

01:04:02.610 --> 01:04:05.321
how about you get it the year after next

01:04:06.072 --> 01:04:07.282
when you turn 30?

01:04:08.575 --> 01:04:09.451
Sorry?

01:04:09.534 --> 01:04:10.702
The thing is,

01:04:10.785 --> 01:04:14.581
Tae-hwan hasn't even made
senior manager in over ten years.

01:04:14.664 --> 01:04:17.250
I'm not saying this because
he and I came in together.

01:04:17.333 --> 01:04:18.793
For our team's morale--

01:04:18.877 --> 01:04:20.295
Did I underperform this year?

01:04:22.005 --> 01:04:24.382
You did great, but…

01:04:25.633 --> 01:04:27.969
If everyone gets the same evaluation,
he won't stand out.

01:04:28.052 --> 01:04:32.390
So if the team members sacrifice a little

01:04:32.474 --> 01:04:35.810
and let Tae-hwan
take the credit, you know?

01:04:36.352 --> 01:04:38.188
You know what I mean, right?

01:04:40.023 --> 01:04:40.940
No, I don't.

01:04:42.734 --> 01:04:45.737
No, you're smart. I'm sure you do.

01:04:45.820 --> 01:04:47.864
Go get Sung-gu for me.

01:04:47.947 --> 01:04:50.283
-Mr. Kim.
-You'll get a good evaluation next year.

01:04:50.366 --> 01:04:51.743
Go get Sung-gu.

01:05:10.303 --> 01:05:11.346
Just to promote you,

01:05:11.429 --> 01:05:13.681
I stalled everyone else
on our team for one or two years.

01:05:13.765 --> 01:05:16.184
What more could I have done?

01:05:16.726 --> 01:05:18.770
I get it. You must feel wronged

01:05:18.853 --> 01:05:20.063
and betrayed by the company.

01:05:20.146 --> 01:05:22.899
Sure, it's inhumane.
Maybe even brutal. I know.

01:05:24.275 --> 01:05:26.444
But come on, the company is not a charity.

01:05:27.403 --> 01:05:30.448
For 25 years, whether you did well or not,
the company paid you every month.

01:05:30.532 --> 01:05:33.826
Sounds to me like the company's done
its share, don't you think?

01:05:41.960 --> 01:05:42.919
Tae-hwan,

01:05:43.670 --> 01:05:45.296
accept the reality now.

01:05:46.047 --> 01:05:47.632
And go find another job

01:05:48.383 --> 01:05:51.052
where you can be treated
with some respect.

01:05:51.553 --> 01:05:53.846
I think that's the right thing to do.

01:05:58.601 --> 01:06:00.478
-Nak-su.
-Yes.

01:06:01.521 --> 01:06:03.731
It looks like you'll become an executive.

01:06:05.233 --> 01:06:07.569
Cut the sarcasm, man.

01:06:10.613 --> 01:06:11.739
I'll get going then.

01:06:28.631 --> 01:06:30.842
Yes. How many times do I have to tell you?

01:06:32.510 --> 01:06:33.428
Yes.

01:06:35.054 --> 01:06:36.472
You made the right decision.

01:06:37.599 --> 01:06:40.810
That's it! We can do this!

01:06:42.895 --> 01:06:43.813
Yes.

01:07:01.205 --> 01:07:06.669
"JUST LIKE HOW YOU LEFT ME WITH A SMILE"
LEE EUN-HA

01:07:07.962 --> 01:07:09.339
Okay, Mr. Choi.

01:07:10.006 --> 01:07:12.508
I'll talk to you later. Okay.

01:07:18.348 --> 01:07:21.351
Nak-su, the conversation went well.

01:07:21.434 --> 01:07:23.061
Whenever there's a government bid,

01:07:23.144 --> 01:07:25.897
the three companies
will pull together from now on.

01:07:25.980 --> 01:07:28.107
That's good news.

01:07:28.191 --> 01:07:29.901
It's all thanks to your hole-in-one.

01:07:29.984 --> 01:07:31.361
Please.

01:07:31.444 --> 01:07:32.862
Everyone just loved the energy.

01:07:34.072 --> 01:07:35.615
-Well done.
-Thank you.

01:07:36.741 --> 01:07:37.992
-Bro.
-Yes.

01:07:38.076 --> 01:07:39.661
I have something to ask you.

01:07:39.744 --> 01:07:41.788
Go on.

01:07:43.247 --> 01:07:46.709
Those cruel HR bastards.

01:07:48.252 --> 01:07:50.046
I think they took it a little far.

01:07:50.129 --> 01:07:52.131
-But Nak-su.
-Yes.

01:07:53.633 --> 01:07:56.302
I'm the one who made the call on Tae-hwan.

01:07:58.763 --> 01:07:59.681
A month ago,

01:07:59.764 --> 01:08:02.558
HR asked me for a list of underperformers

01:08:02.642 --> 01:08:04.268
in the sales division.

01:08:05.812 --> 01:08:07.397
I kind of knew what was going on,

01:08:07.480 --> 01:08:10.066
but I didn't know you made that call.

01:08:10.149 --> 01:08:12.235
I didn't know
they'd ship him off to Ulleungdo.

01:08:12.318 --> 01:08:13.903
That was too harsh.

01:08:15.822 --> 01:08:18.449
I'm the one who handed them the list,

01:08:18.533 --> 01:08:22.203
so I can't exactly go back on my word now.

01:08:22.286 --> 01:08:23.746
You know what I mean, right?

01:08:24.497 --> 01:08:25.373
Sorry?

01:08:27.959 --> 01:08:29.460
Yes, I understand.

01:08:30.002 --> 01:08:31.796
You two started together, right?

01:08:31.879 --> 01:08:32.755
Yes.

01:08:33.798 --> 01:08:36.968
I know you've been helping him
here and there.

01:08:37.635 --> 01:08:39.762
You've done enough.

01:08:39.846 --> 01:08:42.515
It's time to think about yourself
and move on.

01:08:43.307 --> 01:08:44.308
Look.

01:08:44.892 --> 01:08:47.145
You cause a stir over something like this,

01:08:47.228 --> 01:08:49.981
and it will count against
your promotion to executive.

01:08:50.064 --> 01:08:52.191
Tell him to think it over.

01:08:52.275 --> 01:08:54.527
It could be better for him
to walk away now.

01:08:55.194 --> 01:08:58.740
The severance budgets
for voluntary retirement are fixed.

01:08:59.449 --> 01:09:03.161
If he applies late, it will run out.
He won't get anything.

01:09:07.498 --> 01:09:11.085
He might actually be better off
if he opened a dealership or something.

01:09:12.754 --> 01:09:14.756
-I'll talk to him about it.
-Okay.

01:09:14.839 --> 01:09:17.383
Tell him to stay away from trouble.

01:09:18.259 --> 01:09:20.762
I will. If you'll excuse me now.

01:09:20.845 --> 01:09:22.013
-Nak-su.
-Yes.

01:09:22.096 --> 01:09:23.723
I'm feeling the good vibe.

01:09:25.308 --> 01:09:27.769
Let's do well this year

01:09:27.852 --> 01:09:29.520
and deliver great results.

01:09:29.604 --> 01:09:30.772
Okay.

01:09:33.191 --> 01:09:34.525
What the heck?

01:09:38.029 --> 01:09:39.864
They locked down the parking lot.

01:09:42.742 --> 01:09:44.327
What for?

01:09:45.578 --> 01:09:46.913
A SAFETY INCIDENT HAS OCCURRED

01:09:46.996 --> 01:09:48.706
Jeez. I need to get going soon.

01:09:49.373 --> 01:09:50.750
Has there been an accident?

01:10:04.931 --> 01:10:08.351
I just talked to Jeong-tae.

01:10:09.101 --> 01:10:11.395
Hello, is this
Mr. Heo Tae-hwan's emergency contact?

01:10:11.479 --> 01:10:12.355
Sorry?

01:10:12.438 --> 01:10:14.982
It's an emergency.
Are you Mr. Heo's emergency contact?

01:10:16.484 --> 01:10:17.610
Hello?

01:10:18.194 --> 01:10:19.278
Hello?

01:10:21.572 --> 01:10:23.616
Wake up! Hurry!

01:10:52.228 --> 01:10:55.147
THE DREAM LIFE OF MR. KIM

01:11:26.262 --> 01:11:28.723
The reporters seem to have caught on.

01:11:28.806 --> 01:11:31.475
Go and smooth things over in advance.

01:11:31.559 --> 01:11:34.312
I rose through the ranks
without skipping a single promotion.

01:11:34.395 --> 01:11:37.940
And recently,
I secured a major project by myself.

01:11:39.901 --> 01:11:41.652
Nak-su, why is your team falling

01:11:41.736 --> 01:11:44.238
-so far behind Do Jin-woo's?
-Rock, paper, scissors!

01:11:44.322 --> 01:11:47.116
Do you want to join
your father's company after graduating?

01:11:47.199 --> 01:11:48.534
No, of course not!

01:11:49.368 --> 01:11:51.203
How about working with us?

01:11:52.246 --> 01:11:54.332
You survived as a general manager
at a big company,

01:11:54.415 --> 01:11:56.792
bought an apartment in Seoul,
and sent me to college. So what?

01:11:56.876 --> 01:11:58.711
You'll have to choose someone else.

01:11:58.794 --> 01:12:01.923
A senior manager or higher
with over 20 years at the company.

01:12:02.006 --> 01:12:03.591
I'll be an executive next year.

01:12:03.674 --> 01:12:04.675
Awesome!

01:12:04.759 --> 01:12:06.928
I'm 99.9 percent sure. Got that?

01:12:11.349 --> 01:12:13.351
